div.p:
. . . Remember, my brethren . . . ye are free; ye are permitted to act for yourselves;
for behold, God hath given unto you a knowledge and he hath made you free
(Hel. 14:30).

Reproving be times with sharpness, when moved upon by the Holy Ghost; and then
showing forth afterwards an increase of love toward him whom thou host reproved,
lest he esteem thee to be his enemy;
